PuTTY Patch for use with Hercules Console
=========================================

_EITHER_ use the files in folder source to build PuTTY from source
_OR_ simply run it using the ready to run files from folder bin.

Don't use the configuration files in folder sessions for non-APL\360 sessions!
For regular console sessions just start using the default configuration and
switch to passive negotiation on the telnet configuration panel.

source:
-------
putty_hercules.patch           patch for Hercules console compatibility
putty-0.62-source-windows.zip  unmodified source for Windows systems
putty-0.62-source-linux.tgz    unmodified source for Linux/Unix systems

bin:
----
putty-0.62-binary-windows.zip  Windows binaries built from patched source
putty-0.62-binary-linux.tgz    Linux binaries built from patched source

sessions:
---------
APL360_Linux                   Linux parameter file: Copy to ~/.putty/sessions
                               for use with APL\360, don't use for non-APL\360
                               sessions.
APL360_Windows.reg             Windows registry keys: Import into the registry
                               for use with APL\360, don't use for non-APL\360
                               sessions.

----------------
